14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
16 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 353.18B of Title 59, unless
17 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
18 A. Pharmacy technician applicants who are seventeen (17) years
19 of age or older and enrolled in a youth apprenticeship program for
20 pharmacy technicians or a pharmacy technician training program
21 through the Oklahoma Department of Career and Technology Education
22 shall complete Phase II pharmacy technician training in a pharmacy
23 without the requirement to be a pharmacy employee. All pharmacy
24 technician training programs shall be approved by the Oklahoma State
